==法律觀點==
有法律專家認為特朗普向州務卿施壓的言辭已經觸犯了多項選舉法例<ref name=AmySupervilleBrumback/>，包括州法律和聯邦法律中，勾結進行選舉舞弊或妨礙選舉等罪名<ref name="politico-jan3">{{cite web |url=https://www.politico.com/news/2021/01/03/trump-georgia-election-454122 |title=Trump's pressure on Georgia election officials raises legal questions |first1=Allie |last1=Bice |first2=Kyle |last2=Cheney |authorlink2=Kyle Cheney (journalist) |first3=Anita |last3=Kumar |website=[[政客_(媒體)|政客]] |date=2021-01-03 |accessdate=2021-01-03 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103210936/https://www.politico.com/news/2021/01/03/trump-georgia-election-454122}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|author=Eric Lipton|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/03/us/politics/trump-call-georgia.html|title=Trump Call to Georgia Official Might Violate State and Federal Law|newspaper=紐約時報|date=2021-01-03|access-date=2021-01-04|archive-date=2021-01-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210104192131/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/03/us/politics/trump-call-georgia.html}}</ref>。選舉法專家Edward B. Foley指特朗普的行為是不當和可鄙的，{{le|華盛頓公民責任與道德|Citizens for Responsibility and Ethics in Washington}}的執行董事稱，特朗普意圖操縱選舉的行為是美國歷史上的一個下限，無疑是可以受到[[彈劾|彈劾]]的舉動<ref name=PengellyLuscombe>{{Cite web|first=Martin|last=Pengelly|first2=Richard|last2=Luscombe|title='I just want 11,780 votes': Trump pressed Georgia to overturn Biden victory|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2021/jan/03/trump-georgia-raffensperger-call-biden-washington-post|newspaper=衛報|date=2021-01-03|access-date=2021-01-05|archive-date=2021-01-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210105030511/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2021/jan/03/trump-georgia-raffensperger-call-biden-washington-post}}</ref>。

《[[衛報|衛報]]》引述美國憲法教授{{le|Richard Pildes|Richard Pildes}}指特朗普「有意圖目的地要脅州官員敗壞選舉的廉潔」就已經可能觸犯了刑法<ref name="the guardian">{{cite web|last=Sullivan|first=Helen|date=2021-01-04|title=Trump's phone call to Brad Raffensperger: six key points|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2021/jan/04/trumps-phone-call-to-brad-raffensperger-five-key-points|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210104034922/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2021/jan/04/trumps-phone-call-to-brad-raffensperger-five-key-points|archive-date=2021-01-04|accessdate=2021-01-04|work=衛報|quote='You know what they did and you're not reporting it,' Trump said. 'You know, that's a criminal offense. And you know, you can't let that happen. That's a big risk to you and to Ryan [Germany], your lawyer. That's a big risk.' [...] <br/>'''5. Trump may have committed a crime...]''' [Richard H Pildes, a constitutional law professor at New York University, told the Washington Post: "The president is either knowingly attempting to coerce state officials into corrupting the integrity of the election or is so deluded that he believes what he's saying." Trump's actions may have violated federal statutes, he said. [...] <br/>Michael R Bromwich, a former federal prosecutor in the US Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York, wrote: "Unless there are portions of the tape that somehow negate criminal intent, 'I just want to find 11,780 votes' and his threats against Raffensperger and his counsel violate 52 U.S. Code 20511.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Lipton|first=Eric|date=2021-01-04|title=Trump Call to Georgia Official Might Violate State and Federal Law|language=en-US|work=紐約時報|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/03/us/politics/trump-call-georgia.html|access-date=2021-01-04|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2021-01-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210104192131/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/03/us/politics/trump-call-georgia.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |website=[[Law.com|Law.com]] |first=Marcia |last=Coyle |first2=Mike |last2=Scarcella |date=2021-01-04 |url=https://www.law.com/nationallawjournal/2021/01/04/there-must-be-legal-consequences-among-many-lawyers-outrage-over-trumps-georgia-call/ |title='There Must Be Legal Consequences': Among Many Lawyers, Outrage Over Trump's Georgia Call |access-date=2021-01-05 |archive-date=2021-01-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210108015902/https://www.law.com/nationallawjournal/2021/01/04/there-must-be-legal-consequences-among-many-lawyers-outrage-over-trumps-georgia-call/?slreturn=20210007205859}}</ref>。訴訟律師{{le|Michael Bromwich|Michael Bromwich}}指特朗普說「我只想找11780張選票<ref group=原文 name="find 11780"/>」的這句話可能已經觸犯了[[美國法典|美國法典]]{{le|美國法典第52編|Title 52 of the United States Code|第52編}}<ref name="the guardian"/><ref>{{cite tweet |user=mrbromwich |number=1345866768812830724 |title =Unless there are portions of the tape that somehow negate criminal intent, "I just want to find 11,780 votes" and his threats against Raffensperger and his counsel violate 52 U.S. Code § 20511.  His best defense would be insanity. |date=2021-01-03 |first= Browninch| last = Michael}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/52/20511|title = 52 U.S. Code § 20511 - Criminal penalties|quote = (2)knowingly and willfully deprives, defrauds, or attempts to deprive or defraud the residents of a State of a fair and impartially conducted election process, by — (A)the procurement or submission of voter registration applications that are known by the person to be materially false, fictitious, or fraudulent under the laws of the State in which the election is held; or (B) '''the procurement, casting, or tabulation of ballots that are known by the person to be materially false, fictitious, or fraudulent under the laws of the State in which the election is held'''|access-date = 2021-01-05|archive-date = 2021-01-04|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210104204410/https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/52/20511}}</ref>。[[全國廣播公司|全國廣播公司]]則報導特朗普這通電話已經足夠讓調查部門立案研究是否存在利益衝突<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/politics-news/georgia-s-raffensperger-says-he-never-believed-it-appropriate-speak-n1252724 |work=NBC新聞 |date=2021-01-04 |first=Blayne |last=Alexander |first2=Rebecca |last2=Shabad |first3=Shannon |last3=Pettypiece |title=Georgia's Raffensperger says Trump's defeat is the 'cold hard truth,' hints at probe |quote=The Republican secretary of state also said the call from Trump could '''warrant an investigation into possible conflicts of interest'''. |access-date=2021-01-05 |archive-date=2021-01-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210104234207/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/politics-news/georgia-s-raffensperger-says-he-never-believed-it-appropriate-speak-n1252724}}</ref>。

===聯邦===
1月4日，[[民主黨_(美國)|民主黨]]的一眾領袖以特朗普意圖或合謀觸犯選舉法為由，要求[[聯邦調查局|聯邦調查局]]展開調查<ref name="NBC-20210104">{{cite news |last1=Smith |first1=Allan |last2=Moe |first2=Alex |title=Democrats ask FBI Director Wray to open criminal probe into Trump after leaked phone call - Reps. Ted Lieu and Kathleen Rice wrote that they believe Trump "engaged in solicitation of, or conspiracy to commit, a number of election crimes." |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/democrats-ask-fbi-director-wray-open-criminal-probe-trump-after-n1252732 |date=2021-01-04 |work=[[NBC新聞|NBC新聞]] |accessdate=2021-01-04 |archive-date=2021-01-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210104153253/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/democrats-ask-fbi-director-wray-open-criminal-probe-trump-after-n1252732 }}</ref>。儘管有[[共和黨_(美國)|共和黨]]議員認為特朗普只是要求州務卿「尋找合法的選票」，民主黨已經就這次事件著手撰寫{{le|美國譴責決議|Censure in the United States|譴責決議書}}<ref name="CNN-20210104">{{cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/04/politics/trump-call-republican-reaction-censure-resolution/index.html |title=House Republicans rush to Trump's defense over Georgia call as Democrats prep censure resolution |last1=Raju |first1=Manu |last2=Herb |first2=Jeremy |date=2021-01-04 |work=[[有線電視新聞網|有線電視新聞網]] |accessdate=2021-01-04 |archive-date=2021-01-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210104213817/https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/04/politics/trump-call-republican-reaction-censure-resolution/index.html}}</ref>，當1月6日首都國會正在為總統選舉的[[選舉人團|選舉人團]]票點票時[[2021年美国国会大厦遭冲击事件|遭到衝擊佔領]]後，以民主黨為多數派的[[美國眾議院|眾議院]]以「煽動暴力顛覆國家」為由，對特朗普發起[[第二次特朗普彈劾案|第二次彈劾案]]，其彈劾草案中引用了這次電話會議指，這是特朗普「為推翻和妨礙認證2020年總統選舉結果的事前準備」<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/08/politics/trump-article-of-impeachment-draft/index.html|title=Read: House Democrats' draft of a new article of impeachment against Trump|date=2021-01-08|work=有線電視新聞網|accessdate=2021-01-11|archive-date=2021-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109215351/https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/08/politics/trump-article-of-impeachment-draft/index.html|}}</ref>，儘管到參議院的彈劾審判於2月13日無法獲得足夠共和黨參議員支持，讓特朗普獲判無罪。

===喬治亞州===
喬治亞州[[富爾頓縣_(喬治亞州)|富爾頓縣]]地區檢察官{{le|法尼·威利斯|Fani Willis}}於1月4日發表回應指對這次電話會議內容感到不安，她指民主黨的州選舉委員會向州辦事處的選舉分部提出立案調查事件，之後會將案件呈交給州檢察長<ref>{{cite news |last1=Polantz |first1=Katelyn |title=Trump's call could put the President in jeopardy, legal experts say |url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/04/politics/trump-call-legal-jeopardy/index.html |access-date=2021-01-04 |agency=有線電視新聞網 |date=2021-01-04 |archive-date=2021-01-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210104195856/https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/04/politics/trump-call-legal-jeopardy/index.html }}</ref>，當完成調查後案件便會轉交地區檢察辦公室<ref>{{cite news |last1=Polantz |first1=Katelyn |title=Trump's call could put the President in jeopardy, legal experts say |url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/04/politics/trump-call-legal-jeopardy/index.html |access-date=2021-01-04 |agency=有線電視新聞網 |date=2021-01-04 |archive-date=2021-01-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210104195856/https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/04/politics/trump-call-legal-jeopardy/index.html}}</ref>。2月10日，威利斯向包括拉芬斯佩格和坎普等四位喬治亞州官員發出信件，指她的檢察辦公室已經正式調查「意圖妨礙2020年喬治亞州選舉」的相關罪行，並要求官員不要按一般流程銷毀相關文件以備作為呈堂證據<ref "Willis 2020-02-10">{{cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/2021/2/10/22276529/georgia-criminal-probe-trump-prison-fulton-county-fani-willis-election-brad-raffensperger|title=Georgia prosecutors open a criminal probe that could land Trump in prison|date=2021-02-10|accessdate=2021-02-10|work=[[Vox|Vox]]|first=Ian|last=Millhiser|language=en-us|archive-date=2021-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210223094108/https://www.vox.com/2021/2/10/22276529/georgia-criminal-probe-trump-prison-fulton-county-fani-willis-election-brad-raffensperger|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===錄製和公開會談的法律責任和權利===
關於將閉門會議內容錄下並公開的行為，有人指州務卿拉芬斯佩格可能要為此面臨觸犯[[美國1917年間諜法|間諜法]]的起訴。{{le|PolitiFact|PolitiFact}}引述美國保安與憲法法律專家指，特朗普與州務卿的對話不是間諜法涵蓋的國防機密信息，再加上錄音被流出前特朗普事先在社交媒體透露進行過這次會議<ref name=espionage>{{cite web|url=https://www.politifact.com/factchecks/2021/jan/06/facebook-posts/no-grounds-claim-raffensperger-could-face-spy-char/|title=No grounds for claim that Raffensperger could face spy charges over Trump call|publisher=PolitiFact|first=Tom|last=Kertscher|date=2021-01-06|accessdate=2021-01-31|archive-date=2021-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210818114116/https://www.politifact.com/factchecks/2021/jan/06/facebook-posts/no-grounds-claim-raffensperger-could-face-spy-char/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

雖然有謠傳特朗普會就私自錄下會議內容對拉芬斯佩格提出訴訟，但是進行通話的兩端即喬治亞州和首都[[哥倫比亞特區|哥倫比亞特區]]，其{{le|電訊錄音法律|Telephone call recording laws|通訊法}}都允許通訊參與者在不用徵求對方同意下單方面錄下私人談話內容<ref name="one party consent">{{cite web|url=https://en.as.com/en/2021/01/04/latest_news/1609752973_397204.html|title=Donald Trump sues Georgia over call recording: what has he argued?|publisher=[[阿斯報|阿斯報]]|first=Calum|last=Roche|date=2021-01-04|access-date=2021-01-31|language=en|archive-date=2021-02-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210209190312/https://en.as.com/en/2021/01/04/latest_news/1609752973_397204.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Georgia recording law">{{cite web|url=https://www.dmlp.org/legal-guide/georgia-recording-law|title=Georgia Recording Law|publisher=[[哈佛大學伯克曼互聯網與社會研究中心|哈佛大學伯克曼互聯網與社會研究中心]]|date=2021-01-22|access-date=2021-01-31|archive-date=2021-08-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210830152639/http://www.dmlp.org/legal-guide/georgia-recording-law|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="DC recording law">{{cite web|url=http://www.dmlp.org/legal-guide/district-columbia-recording-law|title=District of Columbia Recording Law|publisher=[[哈佛大學伯克曼互聯網與社會研究中心|哈佛大學伯克曼互聯網與社會研究中心]]|date=2021-01-22|access-date=2021-01-31|archive-date=2021-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210924025642/https://www.dmlp.org/legal-guide/district-columbia-recording-law|dead-url=no}}</ref>，由於這次電話會議來得突然，雙方一直沒有在訂立[[保密協議|保密協議]]下通話<ref name="He has no clue"/>。在國會認證總統選舉結果前，沒有任何一單{{le|喬治亞州針對2020年美國總統選舉後的訴訟案|Post-election lawsuits related to the 2020 United States presidential election from Georgia|針對選舉的訴訟}}有提及這次電話會議<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/alisondurkee/2021/01/05/reports-trump-election-lawsuit-against-brad-raffensperger-brian-kemp-fails-in-georgia/|title=Trump Election Lawsuit Against Brad Raffensperger, Brian Kemp Fails In Georgia|publisher=[[福布斯|福布斯]]|date=2021-01-05|access-date=2021-01-31|first=Alison|last=Durkee|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107113308/https://www.forbes.com/sites/alisondurkee/2021/01/05/reports-trump-election-lawsuit-against-brad-raffensperger-brian-kemp-fails-in-georgia/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==林賽·格雷厄姆致電拉芬斯佩格==
拉芬斯佩格向媒體透露，正當喬治亞州於2020年11月11日至20日間進行手動重新點票，共和黨參議員[[林賽·格雷厄姆|林賽·格雷厄姆]]於11月13日私下致電他討論關於這次重新點票的事宜，其中格雷厄姆問他「如果是發生比較多選票簽名錯誤的縣，是否可以取消這些縣的所有[[2020年美国选举邮寄投票|郵寄選票]]的資格？<ref name=Guardian1>{{Cite web | url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/nov/17/lindsey-graham-georgia-ballot-tossing-pressure-condemned | title=Lindsey Graham condemned for allegedly pressuring Georgia to toss out ballots | date=2020-11-17 | access-date=2020-11-20 | work=[[衛報|衛報]] | archive-date=2022-01-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220107155446/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/nov/17/lindsey-graham-georgia-ballot-tossing-pressure-condemned | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Gardner Graham">{{Cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/brad-raffensperger-georgia-vote/2020/11/16/6b6cb2f4-283e-11eb-8fa2-06e7cbb145c0_story.html |title=Ga. secretary of state says fellow Republicans are pressuring him to find ways to exclude ballots |work=[[華盛頓郵報|華盛頓郵報]]| last1=Garder | first1=Amy |date=2020-11-16|access-date=2020-11-17 |archive-date=2020-11-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201117022415/http://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/brad-raffensperger-georgia-vote/2020/11/16/6b6cb2f4-283e-11eb-8fa2-06e7cbb145c0_story.html }}</ref><ref name=Gregorian >{{cite news |last1=Gregorian |first1=Dareh |last2=Clark |first2=Dartunorro |title=Georgia officials spar with Sen. Lindsey Graham over alleged ballot tossing comments |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/georgia-secretary-state-raffensperger-says-sen-graham-asked-him-about-n1247968 |access-date=2020-11-19 |work=[[NBC新聞|NBC新聞]] |agency=[[美聯社|美聯社]] |date=2020-11-18 |archive-date=2020-11-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201118193820/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/georgia-secretary-state-raffensperger-says-sen-graham-asked-him-about-n1247968 |dead-url=no }}</ref>」拉芬斯佩格認為格雷厄姆的意圖是要讓合法選票作廢，但格雷厄姆回應他的目的僅僅是「保護郵寄投票的公正」和確認「郵寄投票如何認證選民簽名」，但拉芬斯佩格對這個辯解不敢苟同表示：「我覺得我在這對話中受到威脅<ref name="Gardner Graham"/>。」格雷厄姆又表示他自己作為參議員正在進行選舉調查，儘管他當時屬於與選舉無關的參議院司法委員會<ref name=Kane>{{cite news |last1=Kane |first1=Paul |title=Lindsey Graham's one-man voting probe prompts confusion |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/powerpost/lindsey-graham-voting-inquiry/2020/11/17/bb67c33c-2917-11eb-9b14-ad872157ebc9_story.html |access-date=2020-11-19 |work=[[華盛頓郵報|華盛頓郵報]] |date=2020-11-17 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201118001253/https://www.washingtonpost.com/powerpost/lindsey-graham-voting-inquiry/2020/11/17/bb67c33c-2917-11eb-9b14-ad872157ebc9_story.html |archive-date=2020-11-18 }}</ref>。喬治亞州富爾頓縣檢察辦公室於2021年2月13日表示，他們會將格雷厄姆致電拉芬斯佩格一事，與特朗普致電拉芬斯佩格事件同樣進行妨礙選舉刑法的調查<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/lindsey-graham-georgia-investigation/2021/02/12/f12faa82-6d6b-11eb-9f80-3d7646ce1bc0_story.html|title=Graham’s post-election call with Raffensperger will be scrutinized in Georgia probe, person familiar with inquiry says|first1=Amy|last1=Gardner|first2=Tom|last2=Hamburger|first3=Josh|last3=Dawsey|work=華盛頓郵報|date=2021-02-13|accessdate=2021-02-13|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213105630/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/lindsey-graham-georgia-investigation/2021/02/12/f12faa82-6d6b-11eb-9f80-3d7646ce1bc0_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

